If fields aren't applicable, they may be ignored.
ENTITY-[ID]-0 shall be in the following format:
[ENTITY ID]
[ENTITY NAME]
[CLASSIFICATION LEVEL]
[AUTHORISATION]
[DATE OF ACQUISITION]

[DESCRIPTION]
[PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS]
[BEHAVIORAL ANALYSIS]
[KNOWN THREATS]
[CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES]
[NOTES]

ENTITY-[ID]-[N] should be in a similar format if possible but may assume that
anyone reading has read ENTITY-[ID]-0 and ENTITY-[ID]-[N] shall have the same
classification as ENTITY-[ID]-0 unless otherwise stated.

Field values:
[ENTITY ID] - A unique identifier for the entity in question.
[ENTITY NAME] - The name given to the entity, if one exists.
[CLASSIFICATION LEVEL] - The level of security required for the entity.
[AUTHORISATION] - ID of the [REDACTED] officer which has authorised, redacted
and classified this document.
[DATE OF ACQUISITION] - Date information on the entity was acquire.
[DESCRIPTION] - A detailed description of the entity, including its physical
appearance and any unique abilities it may possess.
[PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS] - Information on the entity's size, weight, and any
other relevant physical characteristics.
[BEHAVIORAL ANALYSIS] - A description of the entity's behavior and any observed
patterns.
[KNOWN THREATS] - A list of any potential threats posed by the entity, both to
individuals and to the organization.
[CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES] - Detailed instructions for containing the entity,
including any necessary precautions or special considerations.
[NOTES] - Additional notes or observations made by those who have come into
contact with the entity.
